      "cooked": "<p>So I am planning on disabling start and pause for auto-start/stop mode.  This has caused people problems.</p>\n<p><div class=\"lightbox-wrapper\"><a class=\"lightbox\" href=\"https://forums.trainerday.com/uploads/default/original/1X/8e2a8b1d388b37d3793c874f8a5efea80fb56fba.png\" data-download-href=\"https://forums.trainerday.com/uploads/default/8e2a8b1d388b37d3793c874f8a5efea80fb56fba\" title=\"image\"><img src=\"https://forums.trainerday.com/uploads/default/optimized/1X/8e2a8b1d388b37d3793c874f8a5efea80fb56fba_2_592x500.png\" alt=\"image\" data-base62-sha1=\"khEWSs02LDrzDgvhFSXqa8RZ13k\" width=\"592\" height=\"500\" srcset=\"https://forums.trainerday.com/uploads/default/optimized/1X/8e2a8b1d388b37d3793c874f8a5efea80fb56fba_2_592x500.png, https://forums.trainerday.com/uploads/default/optimized/1X/8e2a8b1d388b37d3793c874f8a5efea80fb56fba_2_888x750.png 1.5x, https://forums.trainerday.com/uploads/default/optimized/1X/8e2a8b1d388b37d3793c874f8a5efea80fb56fba_2_1184x1000.png 2x\" data-small-upload=\"https://forums.trainerday.com/uploads/default/optimized/1X/8e2a8b1d388b37d3793c874f8a5efea80fb56fba_2_10x10.png\"><div class=\"meta\"><svg class=\"fa d-icon d-icon-far-image svg-icon\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><use xlink:href=\"#far-image\"></use></svg><span class=\"filename\">image</span><span class=\"informations\">1349\u00d71138 109 KB</span><svg class=\"fa d-icon d-icon-discourse-expand svg-icon\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><use xlink:href=\"#discourse-expand\"></use></svg></div></a></div></p>\n<p>Originally we had this for HR workouts and stuff but now I believe we can improve it.  I have had users press pause then start working out and not noticing workout did not start for example putting app in the background and loosing a workout.  With our setting Disable auto-pause which should be called \u201cDisable Auto-Start/Stop when Power Meter or Trainer is Connected\u201d</p>",
